## Install and load R packages

```r
install.packages(c("sf","gdverse"), dep = T)
# install.packages("devtools")
devtools::install_github("stscl/esp",
                         build_vignettes = TRUE,
                         dep = TRUE)
```


```{r}
library(sf)
library(esp)
library(gdverse)
```

## Equivalence between the Q value and the original geographical detector within the regression framework

```{r}
NTDs = sf::st_as_sf(gdverse::NTDs, coords = c('X','Y'))

system.time({
go1 = esp(incidence ~ ., data = NTDs, discvar = 'none',
          model = 'ols', overlay = 'intersection')
})

system.time({
go2 = gd(incidence ~ ., data = NTDs,
         type = c('factor','interaction'))
})
```

### Factor detector

```{r}
go1$factor
go2$factor
```

### Interaction detector

```{r}
go1$interaction
go2$interaction
```

## Enhanced stratified power model using the spatial linear regression

Using the same data as the gdverse idsa vignette:

```{r}
depression = system.file('extdata/Depression.csv',package = 'gdverse') |>
  readr::read_csv() |>
  sf::st_as_sf(coords = c('X','Y'), crs = 4326)
depression
```

### Enhanced Stratified Power Model With Linear Regression

```{r}
system.time({
  g1 = esp(Depression_prevelence ~ ., data = depression,
         model = 'ols', overlay = 'intersection', cores = 8)
})
g1
```

### Enhanced Stratified Power Model With Spatial Lag Regression

```{r}
system.time({
  g2 = esp(Depression_prevelence ~ ., data = depression,
           model = 'lag', cores = 8)
})
g2
```

### Enhanced Stratified Power Model With Spatial Error Regression

```{r}
system.time({
  g3 = esp(Depression_prevelence ~ ., data = depression,
           model = 'error', cores = 8)
})
g3
```

